import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['width'] = pd.to_numeric(data['width'], errors='coerce')
    data['height'] = pd.to_numeric(data['height'], errors='coerce')
    avg_width = data['width'].mean()
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(['Average Width', 'Average Height'], [avg_width, avg_height], color=['red', 'blue'])
    ax.axhline(avg_width, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Width: {avg_width:.2f}')
    ax.axhline(avg_height, color='blue', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average width and height of the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['values'], ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['values'].min(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {data['values'].min():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['values'].max(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {data['values'].max():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='orange', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title("What is the range of values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Values")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from pandas.api.types import is_datetime64_any_dtype as is_datetime
from pandas.api.types import is_numeric_dtype as is_numeric

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    if is_datetime(data['width']):
        data['width'] = pd.to_datetime(data['width'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
        data = data[pd.notna(data['width'])]
        data['width'] = data['width'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
    if not is_numeric(data['values']):
        raise ValueError('Values must be numeric')
    plt.plot(data['width'], data['values'], color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Values')
    plt.title('Are there any patterns or trends in the values over time?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
